s attention to adventurers carrying coins and gems. Because a xorn isn\'t evil, it pleads or bargains in the hope of convincing owners to give up their treasure, offering up information it has learned from its travels in exchange. A xorn whose requests are ignored might resort to threats and bullying. If starving or angered, it resorts to force.',0,3,0,6,0,0,0,3,0,6,0,0,0,'Senses darkvision 60ft., tremorsense 60ft., passive Perception 16','<strong>Resistances</strong> üèπ and ‚öîÔ∏è from non magical weapons that aren\'t adamantine<br /><br /><strong>Elemental Travelers</strong>&nbsp;Possessed of the power of elemental earth, a xorn glides through stone and dirt as easily as a fish swims through water. It doesn\'t displace earth or stone when it moves, but merges with and flows through it, leaving no tunnel, hole, or hint of its passage.&nbsp;<br /><br />\n<div><strong>Stone Camouflage</strong> The xorn has advantage on Dexterity (Stealth) checks made to hide in rocky terrain.&nbsp;<br /><br /></div>\n<div><strong>Treasure Sense</strong> The xorn can pinpoint, by scent, the location of precious metals and stones, such as coins and gems, within 60 feet of it.&nbsp;</div>','1dungeon,underground,planar','Medium Elemental','[{\"name\":\"Perception\",\"bonus\":\"6\"},{\"name\":\"Stealth\",\"bonus\":\"3\"}]','','[]',NULL,'Xorn.png',NULL,NULL),(872,1,'Yeti','3','40ft., climb 40ft.','12','natural armor','6d10+18',NULL,1,4,1,3,-1,1,-2,4,1,3,-1,1,-2,'Senses darkvision 60ft., passive Perception 13','','arctic,cave,mountain','Large Monstrosity','[{ \"name\": \"Perception\", \"bonus\": \"3\"},{ \"name\": \"Stealth\", \"bonus\": \"3\"}]',NULL,'[]',NULL,'Yeti.png',NULL,NULL),(873,1,'Yochlol','10','30ft., climb 30ft.','15','natural armor','16d8+64',NULL,2,2,2,4,1,2,2,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<strong>Resistances</strong> cold, fire, lightning; üî®, üèπ, and ‚öîÔ∏è from non magical weapons','dungeon,planar','Medium Fiend','[{ \"name\": \"Deception\", \"bonus\": \"10\"},{ \"